Technology:
   Four Software Firms
   To Jointly Develop
   An Interface Standard
"It's a tactical move by Lotus to contain Microsoft and
the inroads it's making in work-group applications," said
David Readerman, an analyst with Lehman Brothers Inc.
   The four-way agreement is an expansion of a cooperative
effort announced last September by Lotus that included Apple
and International Business Machines Corp. An IBM spokesman
said the company supports the revised pact.